abstract: Google has joined a $5.75 million investment round for Pixazza, a start-up that hopes to profit by overlaying photos on the Web with links that let people buy the products in the images.
lead_paragraph: Google has joined a $5.75 million investment round for Pixazza, a start-up that hopes to profit by overlaying photos on the Web with links that let people buy the products in the images.

headline.main: Google Invests in Pixazza, a Start-Up

abstract: Assessing the speed, stability and tab-handling abilities of a new crop of browsers.
snippet: Assessing the speed, stability and tab-handling abilities of a new crop of browsers.
lead_paragraph: IF you’re looking for a good old-fashioned product war, you’re in luck: The browser wars are back on. Last week, Microsoft released the long-awaited update to its Internet Explorer browser. Apple, Mozilla and Google, meanwhile, have lately issued prerelease versions of their coming applications.

headline.main: As Browsers Battle, Consumers Stand to Win
headline.print_headline: As Browsers Battle, Consumers Stand to Win
